&quot;Doubtful stepmother, very doubtful.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uaubard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AU Bard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazons Unite Bard</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/9/01 9:10:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont think so</span><hr size=1> The lesser immortals and mortals watched in awe and with a bit of fear.  Some began to move behind the columns and hide, yet kept an eye on the three powerful goddesses as they argued.  <br>
One such mortal who watched was Paris, a mighty hero.  But, his attentions were not entirely upon the Gods.  Every now and then his eyes would glance to one beautiful woman, who he thought was far fairer than any of the goddesses.  Her name was Helen, one of the many beautiful daughters of Zeus.<br>
The newly wedded couple grew a bit angered that their ceremony was being torn up into a petty feud.  Yet they dared not to speak against the Olympians.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/9/01 9:12:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont think so</span><hr size=1> Hera's cold eyes narrowed.  She was not about to be bested by Zeus's little headache.  As the apple fell into Athena's palm, a slight sizzle sound was heard as it shocked the Goddess of Wisdom's hand slightly.  Then it suddenly began to move up into the air, hovering above Athena. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/9/01 11:07:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I dont think so</span><hr size=1> ~ Artemis gasped as she watched Eris toss the apple and the happening there after, she covered he rmouth and watched, because truthfully, she could not look away. She adored Athena and Aphrodite,and even though Hera and herself had had bad blood in the past, it was all....in the past. She loved and respected her stepmother. No, Artemis was so not going to say anything that would anger any of them.~ <p>Goddess Artemis
