<br>
&quot;Well, now there's the sensible Athena I know and love!  Finally, a brilliant solution.  A judge should be chosen at once and end this petty arguement...&quot;  ::and mumbles aside::  &quot;...and finally let them know once and for all who's the fairest!&quot;   <br>
<br>
::She throws a golden lock of hair behind her shoulders and shows no sign of worry.  She knows she's got this contest in bag.  She scans the room for a judge:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uqueenhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queen Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/12/01 5:25:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not a bad idea....</span><hr size=1> Hera eyed the two other Olympians, and then began to scan the room.  Certainly no fool would go against the Queen of the Gods.  For doing so would bring on a horrid wrath.  And if any of the three where known for wrath, it was Hera.  She folded her arms cooly, slender fingers dancing on one arm as she smirked.  Sure it was just a game that Eris had brought to the wedding.  But, there was rare was the Olympian who would just sit back and give up any contest. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/17/01 10:55:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The God of Truth Tells All</span><hr size=1> A smirk played upon the face of the golden god Apollo. He sat in a gilded chair, amongst the nine Muses. His wrist bobbed back and forth as he juggled a goblet of ambrosia, enjoying the nights festivities. He found it amazing how vanity and arrogance could turn the sweetest rose into a horrid weed. He saw a need to put an end to this, this was a wedding, not a beauty pagent.<br>
<br>
Apollo stood, and the Muses immediatly stepped aside. He cleared his throat and the room grew quiet. Apollo smiled warmly to the rest of the guests, glowling gently with his sun-like aura. He placed his goblet upon a marble table and walked over to Hera.<br>
<br>
&quot;My dearest step-mother. Few can match you sultry beauty, and undeniable sex appeal. You azure eyes burn like a cold flame, and your firey lips glow scarlet like a rare flower. You are indeed among the most pleasent looking females ever to grace Zeus's great universe.&quot; he smiled to his mother and glided across the room to his sister Athena.<br>
<br>
&quot;And Athena! The wise! The ravishing diamond in the rough! None can match you natural beauty. Your light orbs seem to weave a tapestry of brilliant colors and tickle the imaginations of mortal and deity. Your fare skin, light as snow, seemingly of a blank canvas just waiting for an artists hands to come and work upon. Dear daughter of Zeus, and Zeus alone, who could dare challenge your rare and insatiable beauty?&quot;<br>
<br>
He perked a bow and smirked, spinning slowly over to Aphrodite, his oversized sleeves spinning along with him. He grasped the hand of Aphrodite, looking fearlessly into the eyes of the great goddess of all things beautiful and lovely. He lifted his free hands to brush away the few hair that dare to cover her angelic face. <br>
<br>
&quot;All good and well things said about Hera, and Athena;&quot; saying their names he bowed his head to each of them accourdingly, the blushes upon their faces evident.<br>
<br>
&quot;I believe it pales in comparison to the breath taking, and quite frankly freakishly amazing beauty of Aphrodite. Patron goddess to all things beautiful! Besides Hepheastus, and Hermaphrodite all divinities are beautiful in their own right, but none can ever come close to the beauty that is Aphrodite herself. It is as if a power diviner than Zeus's himself, gathered all things wonderful and incarnated them into the fare goddess Aphrodite. Her hair, golden as my own, her eyes blue as Poseidon's seven seas. Skin farer than snow, and lips redder than the reddest apple.&quot;<br>
<br>
He slightly raised Aphrodite's hand and raised his own high in the air.<br>
<br>
&quot;Friends, family, mortals! Here before you lies the most beautiful female figure in the cosmos! As we speak you and I are being basked in her beauty, we are better for having seen her! Hera, Athena, all vanity put aside, you MUST admit that Aphrodite is the farest one of all. The Fates themselves gave her the title. She is goddess of beauty itself, and who better to know beauty than beauty itself! Hera, none are as cunning, Athena, no other is as wise, cultivated and learned as yourself, but all hands down Aphrodite is the most beautiful of all.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo shook the golden hair from his own azure eyes and smiled. He raised her hand to his soft lips and pressed it against them.<br>
<br>
&quot;No other in the land is as beautiful as what I hold before you. So might us continue this party, in peace, and in joy. Eris hand the golden apple to Aphrodite. And we shall continue in merriment this momentous occasion.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo released Aphrodite's hand and perked a brow, surely his speech would cause quite a stir. For affect, he kept his eyes off of Aphrodite, her expression was probably priceless, but nevertheless it would ruin the spontineity of the moment.<br>
<br>
Walking back to his seat, the Muses gasped and whispered among themselves. The pure gaul of Apollo to say such things, such...true things. Never did a untruthful word leave his mouth. They gathered around him, seemingly to protect him from the incomming onslaught.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddesseris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Eris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/17/01 11:31:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/chaoticdiscordxx/images/eris1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The God of Truth Tells All</span><hr size=1> ::: She sat on the table, her legs swining in the air, the smirk on her lips, satisfied so far of her &quot; little game&quot; and where it was going. She almost busted out laughing as the golden bum kisser spoke, she tilted her head listening to his words...Yea, well, Dite might be the goddess of love and beauty, but it didnt mean she was &quot; all that&quot; Plus the fact sometime she had to wear that girdle to sedce a man.....ALLMIGHTY beautiful women didnt need that to do it...but hey....:::<br>
<br>
::Eris stood up on the table::<br>
<br>
All fine and dandy dear Apollo...but that is just your opinion..<br>
I am sure there are many hre that think my beloved mother Hera is the most beutiful, or the ever loved fridged Athena might be...<br>
<br>
::she looked to her father Zeus::<br>
And what do you think we do dear daddy? How do we decide who is the fairest...AND that is what this little game is about...WHO IS THE FAIREST, not the most beautiful...<br>
