::she crossed her arms over her chest, her eyes locked on her father...:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthemuses.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Muses</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/17/01 11:34:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/comedy_of_eros/vircoe05.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Gasping</span><hr size=1> ::The Muses jaws dropped at the controversial speech that Apollo just made.  They all surround Apollo as they stare at him in awe.  Then they stare back at the other immortals, easily reading the clear reactions from all in the room. ::<br>
<br>
::Calliope, the oldest and leader of the muses, steps up to Apollo and in ear shot whispers::  &quot;Apollo, have you've gone mad? I do totally agree with you thoughts but that's what they just should have been-thoughts!  Do you know what you've just done?&quot;  ::She looks at him with pleading eyes and then looks over at the obviously angered Queen of the Gods:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/17/01 11:49:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Calming his Muses...</span><hr size=1> Apollo smiled up at wise Calliope. The most put together of all the nine Muses. He shrugged and sipped from his goblet.<br>
<br>
&quot;I just said what everyone was thinking. And no I have not lost my sanity, someone had to speak up, deture attension away from those three crazed women before they did away with ALL of us.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo shook the hair from his eyes, and looked up at his Muses, his friends, his sisters.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do not worry guys, it will all be ok. IN THE END, it will all be ok. I've seen things ladies, things that will bring about BIG changes in Greece for a long time to come. But I am not at liberty to speak of these things. I must let time take its course. I have discussed such things with my court. The Court of Time, and they assure me of what will happend down to the day. So trust me Calli, all will be fine.&quot;<br>
<br>
His eyes wander over to Eris, and his lip curls in slight disgust. The (and pardon his french) bitch had nothing better to do than to stir up trouble. She was to say the least, pathetic, just like her brother. They were both frowned upon by all atop Olympus, the black sheep of the family. For the love of Zeus didn't they have anything better to do than to piss people off?<br>
<br>
He shrugged and smiled to his Muses, and took out his flute. He began to play a soft, sultry tune with undertones of eastern flare, he had written it for such an occasion, it would calm nerves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugoddessartemis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goddess Artemis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 11:15:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/mogoddessartemis/images/triplemoon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Calming his Muses...</span><hr size=1> ~ Artemis watched her brother act like his typical pompus self. She did love hm dearly, but sometimes he really should curb that ever present ego of his, it was tiring. Artemis foud all three gddesses to be fair, but she wasnt about to say which one she found most fair, that was her personal opinion, as she was keeping it to herself, she didnt want to hurt anyone's feelings, but she had to agre, if that was all possible, with Eris, this contest wasnt about beauty, it was about wh is the fairest, an Artemis didnt really think Dite was.~ <p>Goddess Artemis
Protector of the Amazons
~*~Goddess of the hunt and the Moon~*~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 12:26:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pleased with the outcome</span><hr size=1> Apollo sat in the middle of a now heated conversation with the Muses, the Graces, and ofcourse any old immortal who happend to walk by about the rather impromptu speach he gave. Apollo lifted his hand as if to shush everyone around him. He shook the hair from his eyes and spoke, quietly so that only they could hear:<br>
<br>
&quot;I speak only the truth here tonight. If you think about the word fair...its of both beautiful of body, mind and soul. Now I love them all dearly, but c'mon, none of them are that &quot;fair&quot; to begin with. None of us are. I mean, Hera...psshh, when she goes on a vindictive streak, which by the way is like 5 miles long, she turns into a mad cow, plowing down everyone in her way. The only thing that gleams in her eyes is divine vengance. And being the god of JUSTIFIED Vengence, not that crazy stuff Nemisis is all about...&quot; he shakes his head with a smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Anyway her revenge is rarely justified, or even fun to watch. Its often grotesque and down right mean. And Athena, being the goddess of wisdom she was done some pretty unwise things throughout the course of her life. Down right mean things. Like the whole squabble over Aphrodite trying to weave a tapestry. COME ON! She was just trying to make a tapestry, but Athena had run to Zeus, complaining Aphrodite was trying to steal her patronage.&quot; he rolled his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;And no Aphrodite is no angel. But most of the mean things she's done was either justified, or atleast with a little finess. She is so aloof she rarely holds a grudge, because if you ask me Zeus would be on MY hitlist if he hooked me up with...well you know.&quot; Apollo's lips curled in disgust as he turned and looked at poor, lame, Hephaestus. Sitting there in the corner, alone, again, sipping from his chipped goblet.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now you could say Aphrodite is a little, well...she's premiscuous. But thats only because its her job. If someone gave you a license to flaunce around, flaunting all that you had. I bet you would. Everyone would. Its not &quot;right&quot;, but its justified. And EXCUSE ME, to all those people out there, talking about &quot;fair&quot; and &quot;beautiful&quot; not being the same. TAKE A LOOK AT A DICTIONARY. Its synonemous with beautiful, and the dictionary even goes as far as to say &quot;blonde&quot; rather than &quot;dark haired&quot;. &quot; At this point Apollo, shook the hair from his eyes, just for effect.<br>
<br>
&quot;It also says, the word fair, means...just. Which Hera really is not. She's only  just when her needs are being met. Which don't get me wrong, I'm just as vindictive as my dearest step-mother but I'm not the one in the beauty pagent. Fair means, pleasing to the eye, especially because of fresh,charming or flawless qualities. To the eyes, is not Aphrodite flawless? We're not judging character here, though that does factor in. I mean when you get right down to it fair means superficially pleasing. Which they all are, but if you want to talk perfection. Then look to Aphrodite.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo lifted his goblet to his mouth and sipped, to dampen his throat.<br>
<br>
&quot;They must not have been listening to me. I'm not saying that Dite is perfect. I'm just saying that if you want to talk fair, she is the fairest.&quot;<br>
<br>
