<br>
Nice little speech you had there friend, I totally agree. I love it we you tell it ow it is Apollo. As far as fair goes, which is only looks, Aphrodite takes the cake ::shrugs:: I'm sorry Athena, but if she wasn't the fairest, she wouldn't be the goddess of beauty ::Looks over at Hephaestus, the poor guy. She alays felt sorry that he looked so hideous, because he was such a sweet person. Walks over to him and kisses him on the cheek sweetly, smiles and sits next to him and starts a conversation over platinum::<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 1:28:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Points well taken</span><hr size=1> Apollo smiled and nodded to Nike. They always managed to see eye to eye. He raised his goblet to his lips and sipped slowly, the conversation around him still buzzing. He basically laid it out for people, but he knew they would not listen. This little contest would bring about reprecussions that would be felt centuries from now. Apollo was sure of this, but what those reprecussion would be, his prophecies would not show him. All he knew was they were on the verge of something big.<br>
<br>
He knew that his little outburst would anger Artemis, she was so introverted sometimes. Day and Night they were, totally opposite but had the common ground of the sky. Apollo's outspokeness usually pierced more than a few nerves in Artemis, but those things HAD to be said. Apollo couldn't care anyless whose feelings got hurt, the feelings would heal. He had to speak the truth, what was on everyone's mind anyway. The only reason Athena and Hera are getting all worked up is because they aren't secure in their own beauty, neither is Aphrodite, they suffer the same insecurities most people do. And Eris, took advantage of this. This was her revenge for not being invited to this celebration of union.<br>
<br>
He admired Eris's craftiness, even it was used in a negative fashion, it was her job. And a job is a job. Apollo shook the golden hairs from his eyes. He raised his hands and made sure that his laurel was on and centered and proceeded to walk to the center of the room, standing upon a chair.<br>
<br>
He clapped a spoon against his goblet, again shushing everyone and smiled down to them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Enough of this foolishness. We act like children! Arguing over who is fairer than the next! For shame, it is an opprobrium the way you three act. But I understand why you do so. So I suggest we find a judge, as obviously I am a partial one. I suggest we find, a judge as impartial as one can get!&quot; he sips from his goblet.<br>
<br>
&quot;I say...we ask Zeus! Ofcourse the &quot;Savior Lord of The Sky&quot; will be a fine judge as to whether Aphrodite,Athena, or Hera is the fairest. Don't you all agree? My father, is always right is he not?&quot; with this a wicked smirk appears on Apollo's face.<br>
<br>
&quot;Perfect, then its decided, we will ask Zeus, and he will have the last word to this little squabble.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo stepped off the chair smiling devilishly. He had just placed his father in the hot-seat, and there was nothing he enjoyed more than throwing a kink in his fathers plans. He loved the man, but he was such a sucker. You know they saying, for every seer theres a sucker...well the line was drawn between seer Apollo and sucker Zeus. <br>
<br>
A small laugh escaped him as he almost skipped back to his side of the room, where a large amount of the guests were gathered by now. He smiled brightly and sat in his seat.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 2:10:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Apollo and Nike too</span><hr size=1> She growled lightly making her way towards Hera. It had only been moments since Eris made her appearance and already Hera and Athena were ready to tear Aphrodite to shreds. Sadly, Eris' plan had been working already.<br>
<br>
And even sadder, the others had gotten invollved.<br>
<br>
She glared at Apollo as he spoke his words about Hera, she smiled softly as he spoke of herself of course, but when he made his announcement about Aphrodite, her eyes narrowed into tiny slits glaring at the sun God.<br>
<br>
&quot;Apollo if I didn't love my sister Artemis so much . . .&quot;<br>
<br>
She was angered so greatly at that mere moment that she couldn't speak. Her eyes went wide as Nike agreed with him. Aphrodite would forever endure the wrath of Athena for this. Turning her own companion against her.<br>
<br>
She turned and looked lightly to Hera knowing that this must too be angering the Queen. But then the mention of Zeus was brought into play.<br>
<br>
She turned and faced her Father.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Father, which of us is it indeed?&quot;<br>
<br>
The question they all had been pondering. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 5:55:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/if_the_shoe_fits/itsf254aphrodite27.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A smiles creeps over her face like Apollo's chariot at dawn</span><hr size=1> ::Aphrodite slowly smiles as Apollo flatters the goddess beyond what was nessecary.  She doesn't even respond to Eris' choice of words about her since Apollo boosted her status way high.  She looks over to the others and gives a nod to signify that Apollo is right and then looks towards Zeus.  She raises a brow to see what the King of the Gods have to say in this matter::::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthemuses.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Muses</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/18/01 9:00:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/comedy_of_eros/vircoe05.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ~Apollo's anticts~</span><hr size=1> ::Calliope looks to her sisters and shrugs.  She knows that Apollo's words may be the straw that breaks the camel's back. Clio, who's knowlegde of history is the greatest amongst the sisters, speaks to Apollo in order to talk some sense into him.::<br>
